Grift for life to Mr. Alexander Nory of the feu mails of the lands of Cortachie with the pertinents lying within the diocese of Brechin and sheriffdom of Forfar, formerly granted by the predecessore of the Lord of Brechyn to three chaplainries of the choir of Brechin and six bairns to be sustained at the school to sing in the said choir, with the houses and yards belonging to the saids chaplainries and formerly belonging to Johnne sometime Earl of Mar, as undoubted patron thereof, and now to the King by reason of escheat

through a process of forfeiture of which the said Earl was convicted in Pax-lia- ment. Dated at Falkland 9th September 1584.

preceptum carte confirmationis super carta feudifirme facta per Alexandrum episcopum Brechynensem cum . . . consensu . . . capituli et canonicorum ecclesie cathedralis Breehynensis quondam Dauid Croill in Kethik in vitali redditu . . . ac Andree Oroill suo filio suisque heredibus et assignatis heredi- tarie de . . . quarta, parte . . . terrarum de Kethik cum pertinentiis jacentium in baronia de Kethik infra vicecomitatum de Forfar: tenenda de prefato episcopo et suis successoribus in feudifirma . . . et hereditate imperpetuum etc . Apud Falkland decimo die mensis Septembris anno Domini millesimo quingentesimo octuagesimo quarto .
